background:

I'm new to name servers and wanted to run my *solution* by others.

We (quotron.com) have recently been connected to the internet.
For a long time, we've been getting our mail through uunet via
an MX forward entry and would like to continue doing so.  However,
we would like all non-mail name server requests to be served by
dino.quotron.com which is reachable from the internet.

solution?:

I assume we should setup our name server with an MX mail forward record
pointing mail to uunet.uu.net and to service all other quotron.com 
requests ourselves.

Then we should update the .com name server to use our dino.quotron.com
name server as the primary quotron.com name server and change the
existing quotron.com name servers to secondary?

Does this sound reasonable?

thanks in advance,

--todd booth

